{"title_page": "2016\u201317 Professional U18 Development League", "text_new": "The '''2016\u201317 Professional U18 Development League''' was the fifth season of the [[Professional Development League]] system.\n\n==League 1==\n{{Infobox football league season\n | competition        = U18 Premier League\n | image              =\n | pixels             = 156\n | season             = 2016\u201317\n | winners            = [[Chelsea F.C. Reserves and Academy|Chelsea]] U18s\n | league topscorer   = \n | biggest home win   = \n | biggest away win   = \n | highest scoring    = \n | matches            = \n | total goals        = \n | longest wins       = \n | longest unbeaten   = \n | longest losses     = \n | highest attendance = \n | lowest attendance  = \n | prevseason         = [[2015\u201316 Professional U18 Development League#League 1|2015\u201316]]\n | nextseason         = [[2017\u201318 Professional Development League (Category 1)#U18 level|2017\u201318]]\n}}\n\nThe league was split into two regional divisions, north and south. After playing each team in their own division twice, the league was split into a second league stage consisting of three further divisions. The winning team of Group A in the second league stage became the overall champion and qualified for the [[UEFA Youth League]] for the [[2017\u201318 UEFA Youth League|2017\u201318]] season.\n\n===First League Stage===\n====North Division====\n{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WDL\n|res_col_header=Q\n\n|team1=MCI|name_MCI=[[Manchester City F.C. Reserves and Academy#Academy|Manchester City U18s]]\n|team2=MUN|name_MUN=[[Manchester United F.C. Reserves and Academy#Academy|Manchester United U18s]]\n|team3=LIV|name_LIV=[[Liverpool F.C. Reserves and Academy#The Academy|Liverpool U18s]]\n|team4=BLB|name_BLB=[[Blackburn Rovers F.C. Reserves and Academy#The Academy|Blackburn Rovers U18s]]\n|team5=EVE|name_EVE=[[Everton F.C. Reserves and Academy#Academy|Everton U18s]]\n|team6=DER|name_DER=[[Derby County F.C.|Derby County U18s]]\n|team7=MID|name_MID=[[Middlesbrough F.C. Reserves and Academy#Academy|Middlesbrough U18s]]\n|team8=STO|name_STO=[[Stoke City F.C. Reserves and Academy#Under-18s|Stoke City U18s]]\n|team9=NEW|name_NEW=[[Newcastle United F.C. Reserves and Academy#The Academy|Newcastle United U18s]]\n|team10=WBA|name_WBA=[[West Bromwich Albion F.C.|West Bromwich Albion U18s]]\n|team11=SUN|name_SUN=[[Sunderland A.F.C. Reserves and Academy#Academy Squad|Sunderland U18s]]\n|team12=WOL|name_WOL=[[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C. Development Squad and Academy|Wolverhampton Wanderers U18s]]\n|win_MCI=17|draw_MCI=4|loss_MCI=1|gf_MCI=70|ga_MCI=22\n|win_MUN=14|draw_MUN=4|loss_MUN=4|gf_MUN=63|ga_MUN=31\n|win_LIV=14|draw_LIV=4|loss_LIV=4|gf_LIV=50|ga_LIV=33\n|win_BLB=13|draw_BLB=5|loss_BLB=4|gf_BLB=40|ga_BLB=27\n|win_EVE=11|draw_EVE=6|loss_EVE=5|gf_EVE=49|ga_EVE=35\n|win_DER=10|draw_DER=2|loss_DER=10|gf_DER=38|ga_DER=45\n|win_MID=7|draw_MID=3|loss_MID=12|gf_MID=33|ga_MID=40\n|win_STO=7|draw_STO=2|loss_STO=13|gf_STO=34|ga_STO=49\n|win_NEW=6|draw_NEW=4|loss_NEW=12|gf_NEW=25|ga_NEW=43\n|win_WBA=4|draw_WBA=6|loss_WBA=12|gf_WBA=29|ga_WBA=42\n|win_SUN=3|draw_SUN=4|loss_SUN=15|gf_SUN=23|ga_SUN=55\n|win_WOL=2|draw_WOL=4|loss_WOL=16|gf_WOL=30|ga_WOL=62\n\n|col_G1=#ACE1AF|text_G1=[[2016\u201317 Professional U18 Development League#Group 1|Group 1]]\n|result1=G1|result2=G1|result3=G1|result4=G1\n|col_G2=#D0F0C0|text_G2=[[2016\u201317 Professional U18 Development League#Group 2|Group 2]]\n|result5=G2|result6=G2|result7=G2|result8=G2\n|col_G3=#E0F8E0|text_G3=[[2016\u201317 Professional U18 Development League#Group 3|Group 3]]\n|result9=G3|result10=G3|result11=G3|result12=G3\n|update=complete|source=\n}}\n\n====South Division====\n{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WDL\n|res_col_header=Q\n\n|team1=CHE|name_CHE=[[Chelsea F.C. Reserves and Academy#Academy squad|Chelsea U18s]]\n|team2=ARS|name_ARS=[[Arsenal F.C. Academy|Arsenal U18s]]\n|team3=REA|name_REA=[[Reading F.C. Under-21s and Academy|Reading U18s]