}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Professional U18 Development League 2016-17}}\n[[Category:2016\u201317 in English football leagues]]\n[[Category:Professional Development League|2016-17]]\n", "text_old": "The '''2016\u201317 Professional U18 Development League''' was the fifth season of the [[Professional Development League]] system.\n\n==League 1==\n{{Infobox football league season\n | competition        = U18 Premier League\n | image              =\n | pixels             = 156\n | season             = 2016\u201317\n | winners            = [[Chelsea F.C. Reserves and Academy|Chelsea]] U18s\n | league topscorer   = \n | biggest home win   = \n | biggest away win   = \n | highest scoring    = \n | matches            = \n | total goals        = \n | longest wins       = \n | longest unbeaten   = \n | longest losses     = \n | highest attendance = \n | lowest attendance  = \n | prevseason         = [[2015\u201316 Professional U18 Development League#League 1|2015\u201316]]\n | nextseason         = [[2017\u201318 Professional Development League (Category 1)#U18 level|2017\u201318]]\n}}\n\nThe league was split into two regional divisions, north and south. After playing each team in their own division twice, the league was split into a second league stage consisting of three further divisions. The winning team of Group A in the second league stage became the overall champion and qualified for the [[UEFA Youth League]] for the [[2017\u201318 UEFA Youth League|2017\u201318]] season.\n\n===First League Stage===\n====North Division====\n{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WDL\n|res_col_header=Q\n\n|team1=MCI|name_MCI=[[Manchester City F.C. Reserves and Academy#Academy|Manchester City U18s]]\n|team2=MUN|name_MUN=[[Manchester United F.C. Reserves and Academy#Academy|Manchester United U18s]]\n|team3=LIV|name_LIV=[[Liverpool F.C. Reserves and Academy#The Academy|Liverpool U18s]]\n|team4=BLB|name_BLB=[[Blackburn Rovers F.C. Reserves and Academy#The Academy|Blackburn Rovers U18s]]\n|team5=EVE|name_